Date: Sat, 5 Apr 1997 11:13:45 +0800
From: bunny <rabbit@wantree.com.au>
[See: PRO/AH> Foot & mouth disease - Taiwan (06): China restrictions]
ex Hong Kong Standard, 1 APR 97
Pig disease 'part of mainland plot to launch chemical war'
TAIWAN is investigating if China spread foot-and-mouth disease in pigs to
prepare for a chemical war against the island, the "Independence Evening
Post" says.
"Chemical warfare troops and military intelligence have set up task forces
to probe how the epidemic entered Taiwan and if China is using it to test
the possibility of waging a bio-chemical war on Taiwan," the daily reported
on Monday. The epidemic has alerted the military, even though it cannot
prove it was spread by China to destabilise Taiwan."
On 2 March, the United Morning Post quoted military intelligence as saying
China had ordered 500 tonnes of sarin nerve gas from Ukraine, possibly to
prepare for a bio-chemical war against Taiwan. China has also reportedly
invited former East German chemical warfare commanders and experts to
evaluate the possibility of launching a bio-chemical war on the island.
Despite the Taiwanese claim, Beijing on Monday offered Taipei, through the
Association for Relations Across the Taiwan Straits, a new type of vaccine
to fight FMD. In spite of the pressing need, Taiwan responded coolly to
rival China's offer yesterday to supply vaccines; the two sides have been
political rivals since a civil war split them in 1949. Farm-council
officials questioned the quality of communist China's vaccines and said that
the island had never issued permits to import them from the mainland.
Taiwan is importing eight million vaccines from Britain to vaccinate healthy
pigs and other susceptible stock. Millions of doses were being airlifted in
from Britain, France, the United States and other sources whose production
meets Taiwan's quality requirements.

